The global smart aquaculture market is segmented based on various factors such as component, application, aquatic animal, and farm type. In terms of components, the market is divided into hardware (including sensors, cameras, and monitoring/control systems), software (comprising cloud-based and on-premises solutions), and services (such as consulting, maintenance, and training). When it comes to applications, the market encompasses feeding management, monitoring/control of water quality, inventory management, and disease detection/prevention. Aquatic animals considered within the market include fish, mollusks, and crustaceans. Furthermore, smart aquaculture operations are categorized by farm type, including land-based and offshore facilities.

